arge, indicating electron redistribution)\n\nSo the reaction center involves: C:10, N:20, N:21, C:22, O:23\n\nThe mechanistic class is \"nucleophilic addition\" - specifically nucleophilic 1,2-addition to the azo (N=N) bond.\n\nFor the benchmark, I need to provide a mechanistic label. The most appropriate classification would be:\n\n\"nucleophilic addition\" or more specifically \"1,2-nucleophilic addition\"\n\nGiven the task asks for mechanistic class and reaction center, let me provide both.\n\nActually, looking at the eval contract - it says expected_output_schema is \"mechanistic_label\", so I should focus on the mechanistic class label.\n\nThe mechanistic class: nucleophilic addition (to N=N azo bond)\n\nThis is the key mechanistic step in Mitsunobu reactions where a nucleophile attacks the azodicarboxylate.\n\nLet me finalize: The mechanistic class is \"nucleophilic addition\" - specifically the carbanion nucleophile adds to the electrophilic nitrogen of the azo (N=N) bond of the azodicarboxylate."
